x4freetext: ANU 6 MeV Van de Graaff tandem.
The maximum beam current was 0.5 mu-A.
Two detectors (100 mm2 area and 120 mu-m
depth), mounted in the reaction plane at a distance
of 18.8 cm from the target and 10 degr apart were
used for alpha-particle registration.
Self-supporting natural carbon foils with the
thickness of 10-20 mu-g/cm2.
Two alpha-particles from the decay of
residual Be-8 detected in coincidence.
Excitation energy of the outgoing Be-8.
Excitation energy of the recoil Be-8.
